  "instructions": [
    "Heat sake in a large Dutch oven over medium heat until slightly reduced, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, carrots, and celery, and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.",
    "Add the mushrooms, paprika, and cayenne pepper, and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the chicken broth, tomato paste, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the stew to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 20 minutes.",
    "Season the stew with salt and pepper to taste, then stir in the chopped fresh dill.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional fresh dill if desired.",
    "Let the stew cool to room temperature, then refrigerate or freeze for later use."
  ],
